      • findZeroZPathBuses

        public static java.util.List<BaseAclfBus<?,?>> findZeroZPathBuses(BaseAclfBus<?,?> bus)
        This method is used to find all the buses that are connected to the starting bus through zero-Z branches. It will recursively find all the buses that are connected to the starting bus through zero-Z branches.
        Parameters:
        bus - The starting bus
        Returns:
        A list of buses that are connected to the starting bus through zero-Z branches, including the starting bus itself.

      • findBranchIdDiffs

        public static java.lang.String[] findBranchIdDiffs(java.lang.String originalBranchId,
                                                   java.lang.String changedBranchId)
        from the pattern fromId->toId(cirNo), find the different id parts of the original branch id as compared with the changed branch id.
        Parameters:
        originalBranchId - the original branch id, for example, "Bus13->Bus18(1)"
        changedBranchId - the new branch id, for example, "Bus13->Bus14(2)"
        Returns:
        an array of two strings, where the first string is the fromId part and the second string is the toId part. If the fromId or toId is the same, return an empty string "" for that part.
